.TH DOUBLETAKE-CTL 1 "May 2026" "doubletake" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
doubletake-ctl \- Control doubletake daemon
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B doubletake-ctl
\fICOMMAND\fR [\fIARGUMENTS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B doubletake-ctl
is a command-line interface for controlling the
.B doubletake
daemon. It allows you to query status, connect to and disconnect from Apple TVs,
and manage multiple simultaneous mirroring sessions.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B status
Query the status of the running doubletake daemon and list active connections
.TP
.B connect \fITARGET\fR
Connect to an Apple TV at the specified IP address
.TP
.B disconnect [\fITARGET\fR]
Disconnect from an Apple TV. If no target is specified, disconnects all active connections
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Check daemon status:
.B doubletake-ctl status
.TP
Connect to an Apple TV:
.B doubletake-ctl connect 192.168.1.77
.TP
Connect to multiple Apple TVs:
.B doubletake-ctl connect 192.168.1.77
.B doubletake-ctl connect 192.168.1.100
.TP
Disconnect from a specific Apple TV:
.B doubletake-ctl disconnect 192.168.1.77
.TP
Disconnect all connections:
.B doubletake-ctl disconnect
.SH USAGE
First, start the doubletake daemon in a separate terminal or background:
.IP
.B doubletake \-daemonize
.IP
Then use
.B doubletake-ctl
to manage connections:
.IP
.B doubletake-ctl status
.B doubletake-ctl connect 192.168.1.77
.B doubletake-ctl connect 192.168.1.100
.SH SEE ALSO
.B doubletake(1)
